# GitHub Tooling Precedence

For this repository, prefer `gh` CLI over GitHub MCP for GitHub operations that modify state.

## Project and Repository

- **Repository:** https://github.com/jlmonroy13/gym-voice (jlmonroy13/gym-voice). Use this for scripts, links, and `gh` commands.
- **Project board:** GymVoice (number 3), https://github.com/users/jlmonroy13/projects/3/views/1?layout=board. **Status** options: Backlog, Ready, In progress, In review, Done.

## Prefer gh CLI

Use **gh** CLI by default for:

- creating issues
- editing issues
- adding labels
- creating pull requests
- commenting on issues or PRs
- adding items to the GitHub Project
- updating GitHub Project fields (e.g. Status)
- checking project and issue status when the workflow depends on write-capable GitHub operations

Use GitHub MCP only when:

- the task is read-only, or
- the user explicitly asks to use MCP, or
- `gh` CLI cannot support the required operation cleanly

Before performing write operations with `gh`, verify authentication with:

- `gh auth status`

For project board updates, ensure token has project scope; if needed: `gh auth refresh -s project,read:project`.

## Scripts

- **scripts/task-start.sh N** — Create branch `issue/N-title-slug`; remind to move issue to “In progress.”
- **scripts/task-pr.sh [N]** — Open PR with “Closes #N”; N from arg or from branch name.
- **scripts/task-done.sh [N]** — Remind to move issue to “Done” after merge.

Set `GITHUB_REPO` in the environment or in the scripts if you need a different repo. All scripts default to jlmonroy13/gym-voice.

## Consistency Rule

Do not mix MCP and CLI for the same write workflow unless there is a clear reason. Prefer one consistent execution path per task.
